            "Ten thousand miles she rides to war, crossing mountain passes as though flying. Northern air carries the sound of the watchman\u2019s clapper, cold moonlight shines on iron armor. Generals die in a hundred battles; brave warriors return after ten years.",
            "She returns to see the Son of Heaven, who sits in the Splendid Hall. Her merit is recorded in the highest ranks; rewards of thousands are bestowed. The Khan asks what she desires\u2014Mulan does not want an official post, but wishes to ride a swift steed and be sent back to her homeland.",
            "Father and mother hear their daughter is coming and go out to welcome her; elder sister hears her younger sister is coming and adorns herself by the door; little brother hears his sister is coming and sharpens his knife toward the pigs and sheep.",
            "The buck kicks its feet; the doe\u2019s eyes are half-shut. When two rabbits run side by side, how can one tell which is male and which female?"
